<subSubSection id="C32E54C81609FFDBB59EE56169D7CC72" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="350" pageId="31" pageNumber="347" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8B07431609FFE6B59EE5616A4DCB1C" blockId="31.[160,1156,1606,1701]" box="[160,276,1606,1632]" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis id="B940DB511609FFE6B59EE5616A4DCB1C" bold="true" box="[160,276,1606,1632]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B07431609FFDBB59EE54D69D7CC72" blockId="31.[160,1156,1606,1701]" lastBlockId="34.[160,1156,142,270]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="350" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis id="B940DB511609FFE6B59EE54D6A6CCBFE" box="[160,309,1642,1666]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">Major worker</emphasis>
. Anterior cephalic dorsum striated; posterior half smooth and shining; posterior margin of head strongly concave; eyes small with 10 ommatidia in the longest row; metanotal groove a strongly depressed U-shape; propodeal spines short and acute; petiolar peduncle short; postpetiole massive and glabrous in profile and more than twice broader than long in dorsal view. Head reddish yellow, mesosoma, petiole and postpetiole yellow, gaster brownish yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
